The '''2003 Merapoh bus tragedy''' took place on 23 November 2003 when an Ekspres Mutiara (Pearl Express) bus collided with another bus at kilometre 63 of Lipis-Merapoh Road ('''[[Malaysia Federal Route 8|Federal Route]]''' {{JKR|8}}) near the [[Pahang]]-[[Kelantan]] border, [[Malaysia]]. 14 passengers were killed in this accident.
Among those killed were a two-year-old girl, eight women and five men.
