{{Infobox Convention | name = MangaNEXT | image = | caption = | status = Inactive | venue = Sheraton Meadowland Hotel & Convention Center | location = [[East Rutherford, New Jersey]] | country = United States | first = 2006 | last = 2012 | organizer = Universal Animation, Inc.<ref name="AC-UA">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/organizer/73/universal-animation-inc- | title = Universal Animation, Inc. Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2018-10-03}}</ref><ref name="MN2006-PR">{{cite press release | title = MangaNEXT announced for the first weekend of October | publisher = AnimeCons.com | date = 2006-07-12 | url = https://animecons.com/press/post/333/manganext-announced-for-the-first-weekend-of-october | accessdate = 2018-06-04 }}</ref> | filing = 501(c)(3)<ref name="MN2006-PR"/> | attendance = 1,070 in 2006 | events = | website = http://www.manganext.org/ }}
'''MangaNEXT''' is an inactive [[fan convention]] focused exclusively on Japanese [[manga]] that occurred every other year in [[New Jersey]].<ref name="pw02282012">{{cite news | work = Publishers Weekly | title = Fans, Publishers, Creators Gather at the MangaNEXT Convention | date = 2012-02-28 | first = Brigid | last = Alverson | url = http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/comics/article/50817-fans-publishers-creators-gather-at-the-manganext-convention.html | accessdate = 2013-02-10}}</ref> It is the only manga convention in the United States.<ref name="tr10042007">{{cite news | work = The Record | title = U.S. bitten by the manga bug; Following grows for Japanese comics | date = 2007-10-04 | first = Evelyn | last = Shih }}</ref><ref name="pw11042008"/>
==Programming== The convention typically offers an artists alley, burlesque show, dealer's room, and swap meet.<ref name="pw11042008"/>
==History== MangaNEXT was located at the Crowne Plaza Meadowlands in Secaucus, New Jersey for 2007.<ref name="tr10042007"/> In 2008 the convention moved to the Doubletree Somerset Hotel in Somerset, New Jersey for additional space, but suffered from some disorganization and poor communication.<ref name="pw11042008">{{cite news | work = Publishers Weekly | title = A Small MangaNext Con Grows in Somerset, N.J. | date = 2008-11-04 | first = Erin | last = Finnegan | url = http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/new-titles/adult-announcements/article/16301-a-small-manganext-con-grows-in-somerset-n-j.html | accessdate = 2013-02-10}}</ref> The convention in 2012 moved to the Sheraton Hotel in East Rutherford, New Jersey, which had no public transit access.<ref name="pw02282012"/>
